title: Tidal flood reports from Norfolk, Virginia, USA
text:
Tidal flood reports from Norfolk, Virginia, USA   
Sep 27, 2015 eTN   
A significant tidal flooding has been reported in Norfolk, Virginia this evening 
A Coastal Flood Warning remains in effect until 1 PM EDT Sunday for Norfolk, Virginia, USA 
The exact location is calculated for Southside Hampton Roads and locations along the James River. 
Minor to moderate coastal flooding could be expected during high tide this evening and Sunday morning. 
Flooding in the coastal areas could lead to road closures and flooding of property. 
Norfolk is an independent city in the Commonwealth of Virginia, United States of America. 
Norfolk is known to residents and tourists as a vibrant, waterfront city in the heart of Coastal Virginia. City leaders think visitors will discover that Norfolk is a Distinct, Dynamic and Diverse place to live, work and play.
